		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=299733"><span id=Sage>Saboruto</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="73" src="/uf/Saboruto/myavatar.gif"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />2216 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Saboruto&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>There are two ways, but they both amount to the same thing.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have to do a level 2 effect, and then another lv. 2 weaponskill after that.  What that means is, you have to combine Fragmentation with Fusion to make Light, or Gravitation and Distortion to make Dark.  Here are two scenarios:<br><br>1) I have a RNG and a THF.  The RNG opens the weaponskill with Arching Arrow (which, being a 225+ weaponskill, has a level 2 innate elemental property, in this case Fusion).  Because the RNG has opened with a weaponskill that is charged with fusion all by itself, we're already set up for the next weaponskill to activate Light.  The THF uses Shark Bite (which is Fragmentation all by itself) and the combination of Fusion and Fragmentation activates Light.  Our skillchain in this example is Arching Arrow &gt;&gt; Shark Bite.<br><br>2) Unfortunately, our RNG has to leave.  However, we can still make a Light chain!  In this situation, we're going to be starting with a pair of lower level weaponskills to make Fusion the old fashioned way.  Our PLD will open the chain with Red Lotus Blade.  Then our MNK is going to use Combo.  Now, RLB &gt; Combo will do Fusion.  Since Fusion is now in play, the THF can use Shark Bite to add Fragmentation to the mix, and again we have a Lv. 3 Light chain.  Our skillchain in this example is Red Lotus Blade &gt;&gt; Combo &gt;&gt; Shark Bite.<br><br>Now, obviously the first scenario is a lot easier to pull off, since it will only require two people to have enough TP to open the chain.  However, a lot of times you just don't have the right jobs to do a 2-man Lv.3 chain.  In those cases, three people can do the job as well.<br><br>The key is to start off with a level 2 effect (Fusion, Distortion, Fragmentation or Gravitation).  Then, you have to add its partner effect (Fusion &lt;--&gt; Fragmentation or Distortion &lt;--&gt; Gravitation).  And because of the laws of skillchaining, you HAVE to make the last weaponskill the 225+ one, or else the lv. 3 chain won't work.<br><br>I hope I explained that ok, it's a little complicated until you really see it in action.  For reference, here are the 225+ weaponskills and what element they're attached to:<br><br>Fragmentation (thunder+wind):<br>Black Halo (club)<br>Shark Bite (dagger)<br>Evisceration (dagger)<br>Dragon Kick (H2H)<br>Savage Blade (sword)<br>Spinning Slash (g.sword)<br>Ground Strike (g.sword)<br><br>Gravitation (darkness+earth):<br>Asuran Fists (H2H)<br>Blade: Ten (katana)<br>Blade: Ku (katana)<br>Impulse Drive (polearm)<br>Retribution (staff)<br>Swift Blade (sword)<br><br>Fusion (fire+light):<br>Mistral Axe (axe)<br>Decimation (axe)<br>Arching Arrow (bow)<br>Empyrial Arrow (bow)<br>Hexa-Strike (club)<br>Tachi: Kasha (g.katana)<br>Heavy Shot (marksmanship)<br>Detonator (marksmanship)<br>Wheeling Thrust (polearm)<br><br>Distortion (water+ice):<br>Full Break (g.axe)<br>Steel Cyclone (g.axe)<br>Tachi: Gekko (g.katana)<br>Cross Reaper (scythe)<br>Spiral Hell (scythe)<br>Ground Strike (g.sword)</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Blah.&nbsp;&nbsp;Someone say something interesting/witty/scathing about me so I can quote you.  I'm bored with Twiz's "God hates fags" quote.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Athens, Georgia, USA</td></tr></table>
